title: Grain lower, livestock higher
text:
Tue, Aug 4, 2015, 1:07 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 8 hrs 53 mins Grain lower, livestock higher Grain lower on the CBOT, beef and pork higher on the CME Associated Press â€“ 18 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were lower in early trading Monday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was 7.5 cents lower at $4.9175 a bushel; December corn was 4 cents lower at $3.7725 a bushel; December oats were 9.25 cents lower at $2.4775 bushel; while November soybeans fell 8.25 cents to 9.32 cents a bushel. 
Beef and pork were higher on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was 2.025 cents higher at $1.4795 a pound; August feeder cattle was 2.70 cents higher at $2.13425 a pound; October lean hogs rose .575 cent to $.6430 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Terms
